The movie had a some unresolved plot that wasn't answered for (for example, without spoilers, I believe Finn tried to tell Rey something personal, was interrupted, and never attempted to tell her again... what was it? I was never bullied or shunned for being a fan, but I too have had my share of being bullied once or twice during my high school years just from being a nice guy to others who saw it as weakness or being a naive pushover not having an aggressive attitude so I can relate.

I have my nitpicks of Episodes 7-9, more so with 8, but I overall enjoy them, including the prequels, but I have gotten comfortable with the fact that no one is ever going to be on the same side of enjoying everything Star Wars without hating or disliking something for bad or good reason. Plain and simple. What it comes down to is treating others with “respect.” To force (pun intended, lol) your own opinions on someone concerning the franchise without respecting the other’s opinions as they would respect your own is being arrogant and a bully.

That’s why I always enjoy watching your content. You are respectful to your fans and the fact you have a massive subscriber count shows that many are respectful to you in return, even if we may disagree with things from time to time.
